{"title_page": "Kitne Door Kitne Paas", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Unreferenced|date=June 2007}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Kitne Door Kitne Paas\n| image          = Kitne_Door_Kitne_Paas_poster.jpg\n| image_size     =\n| caption        = DVD cover\n| director       = [[Mehul Kumar]]\n| producer       = [[Mehul Kumar]]\n| writer         = [[Mehul Kumar]],<br>Imtiaz Patel,<br>Yunus Sejawal\n| narrator       =\n| starring       = [[Fardeen Khan]]<br />[[Amrita Arora]]\n| music          = [[Sanjeev Darshan]]\n| cinematography = Mazhar Kamran\n| editing        = Yusuf Sheikh\n| studio         = MK Pictures\n| distributor    = \n| released       = 29 March 2002\n| runtime        = \n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = [[Hindi language|Hindi]]\n| budget         = {{INRConvert|30|c|year=2002}}\n| gross          = {{INRConvert|2.2|c|year=2002}}\n| preceded_by    =\n| followed_by    =\n| website        =\n}}\n\n'''''Kitne Door Kitne Paas''''' (\u0915\u093f\u0924\u0928\u0947 \u0926\u0942\u0930 \u0915\u093f\u0924\u0928\u0947 \u092a\u093e\u0938) ([[English language|English]]: ''How Far How Near'') is an Indian Hindi [[romance film]] released in [[2002 in film|2002]]. It stars [[Fardeen Khan]] and [[Amrita Arora]] in the lead roles.\n\n== Story ==\nTwo young Indians, a male named Jatin, and a woman named Karishma, meet on an airplane, who are on their way to India. Jatin is returning home to marry Jaya, who has been chosen for him by his mother. Karishma is also returning to India to marry an Indian named Nimesh. Their paths cross, and despite of the difference in their temperaments, both are attracted to each other. Both would like to get married, but also realize and stand by their commitment to Jaya and Nimesh. Also the parents are against the marriage at first but then Jaya at the wedding explains how one cannot be forced into marriage and she didn't want to marryJatin. A fire then starts and Jatin saves Karishma and Nimesh backs out so her father thinks Jatin is better for her and Jatin and Karishma marry at the end.\n\n==Cast==\n\n*[[Fardeen Khan]]... Jatin\n*[[Amrita Arora]]...  Karishma\n*[[Ayub Khan (actor)|Ayub Khan]]...  Nimesh\n*[[Sonali Kulkarni]] ...  Jaya Patel\n*[[Satish Shah]] ...  Veer Singh / Jeet Singh Rathod / Bhanwar Singh\n*[[Ketki Dave]] ...  Koki, Jaya's mother\n*[[Tiku Talsania]] ...  Babu Patel\n*[[Govind Namdeo]]\n*[[Beena Banerjee|Beena]] ...  Rama\n*[[Ram Mohan]]\n*[[Lilette Dubey]]\n*[[Shehzad Khan]] ... Police Inspector K.K. Limbachia\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{| border=\"4\" cellpadding=\"7\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" align=\"center\"\n! # !! Title !! Singer(s) !! Lyricist(s)\n|-\n| 1\n| \"Kitne Door Kitne Paas\"\n| [[Udit Narayan]], [[Kavita Krishnamurthy]]\n| [[Anand Bakshi]]\n|- \n| 2\n| \"Rulati Hain Mohabbatein\" \n| [[KK (singer)|KK]]\n| Anwar Sagar\n|- \n| 3\n| \"Diwana Dil Hain Mera\"\n| [[Sonu Nigam]], [[Sunidhi Chauhan]]\n| [[Abbas Tyrewala]]\n|- \n| 4\n| \"Yaar Mein India Chala\" \n| Sonu Nigam, [[Mohammed Aziz]]\n| Anand Bakshi\n|- \n| 5\n| \"Ji Jeend Jaan\"\n| Sonu Nigam, [[Alka Yagnik]]\n| Anand Bakshi\n|- \n| 6\n| \"Humko Mohabbat Dhoondh Rahi\"\n| [[Roop Kumar Rathod]]\n| Anand Bakshi\n|}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|0313395|Kitne Door Kitne Paas}}\n\n[[Category:2000s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:2002 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n\n\n{{2000s-Hindi-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Unreferenced|date=June 2007}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Kitne Door Kitne Paas\n| image          = Kitne_Door_Kitne_Paas_poster.jpg\n| image_size     =\n| caption        = DVD cover\n| director       = [[Mehul Kumar]]\n| producer       = [[Mehul Kumar]]\n| writer         = [[Mehul Kumar]],<br>Imtiaz Patel,<br>Yunus Sejawal\n| narrator       =\n| starring       = [[Fardeen Khan]]<br />[[Amrita Arora]]\n| music          = [[Sanjeev Darshan]]\n| cinematography = Mazhar Kamran\n| editing        = Yusuf Sheikh\n| studio         = MK Pictures\n| distributor    = \n| released       = 29 March 2002\n| runtime        = \n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = [[Hindi language|Hindi]]\n| budget         = {{INRConvert|30|c|year=2002}}\n| gross          = {{INRConvert|2.2|c|year=2002}}\n| preceded_by    =\n| followed_by    =\n| website        =\n}}\n\n'''''Kitne Door Kitne Paas''''' (\u0915\u093f\u0924\u0928\u0947 \u0926\u0942\u0930 \u0915\u093f\u0924\u0928\u0947 \u092a\u093e\u0938) ([[English language|English]]: ''How Far How Near'') is an Indian Hindi [[romance film]] released in [[2002 in film|2002]]. It stars [[Fardeen Khan]] and [[Amrita Arora]] in the lead roles.\n\n== Story ==\nTwo young Indians, a male named Jatin, and a woman named Karishma, meet on an airplane, who are on their way to India. Jatin is returning home to get married to a woman named Jaya, who has been chosen for him by his mother. Karishma is also returning to India to get married to an Indian named Nimesh. Their paths cross, and despite of the difference in their temperaments, both are attracted to each other. Both would like to get married, but also realize and stand by their commitment to Jaya and Nimesh. Also the parents are against the marriage at first but then Jaya at the wedding explains how one cannot be forced into marriage and she didn't want to get married to Jatin. A fire then starts and Jatin saves Karishma and Nimesh backs out so her father thinks Jatin is better for her and Jatin and Karishma get married at the end.\n\n==Cast==\n\n*[[Fardeen Khan]]... Jatin\n*[[Amrita Arora]]...  Karishma\n*[[Ayub Khan (actor)|Ayub Khan]]...  Nimesh\n*[[Sonali Kulkarni]] ...  Jaya Patel\n*[[Satish Shah]] ...  Veer Singh / Jeet Singh Rathod / Bhanwar Singh\n*[[Ketki Dave]] ...  Koki,